data.conversation: Can you tell me about the welfare service for individuals who have suffered severe injuries and need assistance with daily activities?
data.translation: 중상을 입은 사람들이 일상 활동을 도움 없이 수행하기 어려운 경우에 대한 복지 서비스에 대해 이야기해 주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for elderly individuals aged 65 and above who have mobility difficulties due to old age or illness and live alone or with an elderly spouse. It is also available for surviving patriots, spouses of surviving patriots, and first-class disabled veterans, regardless of their living standards. However, individuals who are already receiving similar home care services through national projects are excluded from this service.
data.conversation: Can you tell me who is eligible for the home welfare support service for the elderly? I heard it is for elderly individuals who have difficulty moving due to old age or illness and live alone or with an elderly spouse. Is that correct?
data.translation: 노인을 위한 가정 복지 지원 서비스에 대해 누가 자격이 있는지 알려주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for elderly individuals who are 65 years old or older for men, and 60 years old or older for women, and do not have any caregivers. It is also available for certain priority groups such as veterans, disabled individuals, and the families of deceased veterans.
data.conversation: Do you know of any services available for elderly individuals who don't have any caregivers and are 65 years old or older for men, and 60 years old or older for women? I heard that there are also services for veterans, disabled individuals, and the families of deceased veterans.
data.translation: 부양의무자가 없는 65세 이상 남성 또는 60세 이상 여성을 위한 서비스가 있는지 알고 계세요?

data.description: This service is for individuals who are eligible for government-funded medical treatment or reduced medical fees, such as veterans, war heroes, and their families.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the medical treatment services available for veterans and war heroes?
data.translation: 군인들을 위한 의료 서비스에 대해 알려주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for individuals who are eligible for national benefits, such as veterans, those injured in democratic movements, and individuals with health issues related to exposure to defoliant. It provides a discount on LPG fuel for prosthetic vehicles.
data.conversation: Do you know if there is any support available for veterans, those injured in democratic movements, or individuals with health issues related to exposure to defoliant? I heard there is a discount on LPG fuel for their prosthetic vehicles.
data.translation: 국가유공자인데 국가 혜택을 받을 수 있는 사람들에게 어떤 지원이 있는지 알고 있나요? 그들의 보철용 차량에 LPG 연료에 할인이 있다고 들었어요.

data.description: This service is for individuals who are eligible for various discounts on their communication fees, including phone calls, internet calls, and mobile phone fees.
data.conversation: Do you know if there are any discounts available for communication fees? I heard that certain groups of people are eligible for reduced fees on phone calls, internet calls, and mobile phone fees.
data.translation: 보훈대상자인데 통신요금에 할인이 가능한지 아세요?

data.description: This service is for individuals who are national merit recipients, veterans, or have disabilities related to their service, as well as their spouses, children, and parents.
data.conversation: Can you tell me who is eligible for the national merit recipient employment development support?
data.translation: 국가유공자인데 직장이 없고 취직하고 싶어요.

data.description: This service is for discharged military personnel who are actively seeking employment after being unemployed for a certain period of time.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the support provided to discharged military personnel who are actively seeking employment?
data.translation: 실업 상태에서 적극적으로 구직활동을 하는 퇴역한 군인에게 제공되는 지원에 대해 말해주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for individuals who are eligible for education support under the national veterans' affairs laws, including veterans themselves, spouses of deceased veterans, and children of deceased veterans (including grandchildren in the case of independent veterans). The service provides annual learning support funds for middle school, high school, and university education, as well as lifelong education facilities and credit recognition institutions.
data.conversation: Who is eligible for the education support funds under the national veterans' affairs laws? What types of educational institutions are covered by the annual learning support funds? How can eligible individuals receive the funds?
data.translation: 국가보훈법에 따라 교육지원을 받고 싶어요.

data.description: This service is for families who are facing economic or social crises and need support to strengthen their family functions and capabilities.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about a service that provides support for families facing economic or social crises?
data.translation: 경제적이거나 사회적 위기에 직면한 가족들을 지원하여 가족 기능과 역량을 강화하는 서비스에 대해 이야기해주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for low-income individuals, newlyweds, and young people who need assistance with purchasing or renting affordable housing.
data.conversation: Can you tell me more about the support available for low-income individuals, newlyweds, and young people who need affordable housing?
data.translation: 저소득층, 신혼부부 및 청년들이 저렴한 주택을 구매하거나 임대하는 데 도움이 필요한 경우에 대한 지원에 대해 더 알려주시겠어요?

desc.title: 기존주택 일반 저소득층·신혼부부·청년 등 매입임대주택 지원

data.description: This service is for individuals or families who are living in non-residential places such as small rooms, boarding houses, or vinyl houses for more than 3 months, as well as victims of domestic violence, crime, and households with children under 18 years old who do not meet the minimum housing standards.
data.conversation: Can you help me find affordable rental housing if I have been living in a small room for more than 3 months? I am also a victim of domestic violence and have a child under 18 years old.
data.translation: 3개월 이상 작은 방에서 살고 있고, 저렴한 임대 주택을 찾는 데 도움을 받을 수 있을까요?

data.description: This service is for owners of buildings with slate roofs and walls, providing support for the removal and disposal of slate roofing and assistance with improvement for vulnerable groups.
data.conversation: I have a building with a slate roof and walls, and I need help with removing and disposing of the slate roofing. Can you also assist with improvements after the removal?
data.translation: 저는 슬레이트 지붕과 벽을 가진 건물을 소유하고 있고, 슬레이트 지붕을 제거하고 처분하는 데 도움이 필요합니다.

data.description: This service is for homeowners who wish to install renewable energy facilities such as solar power, solar heat, geothermal, fuel cells, and small wind power. They can receive partial financial support for the installation costs.
data.conversation: Do you know if there is any support available for homeowners who want to install renewable energy facilities like solar power or geothermal? I heard they can get some financial assistance for the installation costs.
data.translation: 신재생에너지 시설 설치를 원하는 주택 소유자들을 위한 지원이 있는지 알고 있나요? 태양광이나 지열과 같은 신재생에너지 시설을 설치하려는 사람들은 설치 비용에 일부 금전적 지원을 받을 수 있다고 들었어요.

data.description: This service is for households facing financial difficulties, such as those receiving welfare benefits or support for disabilities, and provides support for indoor environmental pollution diagnosis and consulting, as well as eco-friendly home improvement.
data.conversation: I heard there is a service that helps households with financial difficulties improve their living environment. Can you tell me more about it?
data.translation: 어려운 경제사정을 겪고 있는 가구들을 위해 실내환경 오염 진단 및 컨설팅, 친환경 주거개선을 지원하는 서비스가 있다고 들었는데요. 더 자세한 내용을 알려주실 수 있을까요?

data.description: This service is for individuals who are 19 years or older, without a home or owning only one home with a value of 900 million won or less.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the housing loan program for individuals who are 19 years or older and do not own a home or own only one home with a value of 900 million won or less?
data.translation: 19세 이상이고 주택을 소유하지 않거나 900억 원 이하의 가치를 가진 주택을 소유한 사람들을 위한 주택 대출 프로그램에 대해 알려주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for individuals or couples who have a monthly rent of 600,000 won or less and a total net asset value of 320 million won or less, and have signed a monthly rental contract for a house with a deposit of 100 million won or less and a floor area of 85㎡ or less (100㎡ for rural areas).
data.conversation: Do you know anyone who is looking for a low-interest loan for their monthly rent? They should have a monthly rent of 600,000 won or less and a total net asset value of 320 million won or less, and have signed a monthly rental contract for a house with a deposit of 100 million won or less and a floor area of 85㎡ or less (100㎡ for rural areas).
data.translation: 월세가 적은데 주택 월세계약을 체결한 부부예요. 월세 대출을 받을 수 있을까요?

data.description: This service is for individuals who have signed a lease agreement with a rental deposit of 700 million won or less (500 million won or less in local areas) and have paid at least 5% of the rental deposit.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the eligibility criteria for the rental deposit guarantee service?
data.translation: 전세 자금 보증이 필요해요.

data.description: This service is for single-parent families and their dependents, excluding those who receive livelihood and medical benefits, as well as children under the age of 13.
data.conversation: Who is eligible for the small insurance for single-parent families and their dependents? Can they claim insurance benefits for injuries or illnesses that occur during the insurance period?
data.translation: 한부모가족인데 보험이 필요해요.

data.description: This service is for low-income pregnant women who have been diagnosed with high-risk pregnancy conditions and have received hospital treatment.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the support for medical expenses for high-risk pregnant women?
data.translation: 고위험 임산부인데 의료비 지원을 받고 싶어요.

data.description: This service is for pregnant women to receive influenza vaccination.
data.conversation: Do pregnant women have access to free influenza vaccination?
data.translation: 임신부는 무료로 인플루엔자 예방접종을 받을 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for pregnant women, new mothers, and parents of children under 2 years old who are covered by health insurance and need financial assistance for medical expenses related to pregnancy and childbirth.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the welfare service that provides financial assistance for medical expenses during pregnancy and childbirth for those covered by health insurance?
data.translation: 신생아의 엄마인데 복지 서비스에 대해 알려주세요.

data.description: This service is for unmarried or divorced single parents who do not have the consent for adoption during the adoption waiting period (7 days after childbirth).
data.conversation: Do you know if there is any support available for single parents who are unable to give consent for adoption during the adoption waiting period?
data.translation: 아이를 낳은지 얼마 안 됐어요. 지원이 있는지 알고 계세요?

data.description: This service is for women who are not eligible for maternity leave benefits due to not being covered by employment insurance.
data.conversation: I heard there is a service that provides support for women who are not covered by employment insurance and cannot receive maternity leave benefits. Do you know anything about it?
data.translation: 고용보험에 가입되지 않아 출산 휴가급여를 받을 수 없는 여성을 위한 지원 서비스가 있다고 들었어요.

data.description: This service is for employers or employer organizations who have subscribed to employment insurance and need financial support for establishing workplace childcare facilities.
data.conversation: Do you know if there is any support available for employers who want to set up workplace childcare facilities?
data.translation: 직장어린이집을 설립하려는 사업주들에게 어떤 지원이 있는지 알고 계신가요?

data.description: This service is for parents or guardians who are taking care of children aged 0-6 years old at home without receiving support for childcare fees, preschool fees, or full-day childcare services.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the welfare service that provides support for parents who are taking care of young children at home without receiving any financial assistance?
data.translation: 별다른 지원 없이 0~6세 영유아를 양육하는 부모나 보호자를 위한 복지 서비스에 대해 알려주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for teenage parents who have children and have an income below 60% of the median income.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the support for teenage parents who have children and low income?
data.translation: 아이를 가진 가난한 청소년 부모인데 양육비가 모자라요. 이에 대해 알려주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for all parents and children before they start school, providing support such as childcare counseling, temporary childcare services, book and toy rental, play spaces, and parent networking.
data.conversation: Do you know of any centers that provide comprehensive support for childcare, including counseling, temporary childcare services, and resources like books and toys?
data.translation: 육아 상담, 놀이 공간 및 부모 간 교류와 같은 종합적인 육아 지원을 제공하는 센터를 아시나요?

data.description: This service is for families with newborns who have congenital metabolic disorders or infants under the age of 19 diagnosed with rare diseases or other conditions.
data.conversation: Do you know if there are any welfare services available for families with newborns who have congenital metabolic disorders or infants diagnosed with rare diseases?
data.translation: 선천성 대사 이상을 가진 신생아를 가진 가족이나 희귀 질환을 진단받은 영아를 위한 복지 서비스가 있는지 알고 계신가요?

data.description: This service is for parents of premature or underweight babies, providing a reduction in out-of-pocket expenses for medical treatment until the child turns 5 years old.
data.conversation: Have you heard about the welfare service that reduces the medical expenses for parents of premature or underweight babies until the child turns 5? It's really helpful for families who have to deal with the financial burden of medical treatments.
data.translation: 아이를 낳았는데 저체중이에요. 부모를 위한 의료비 경감 복지 서비스에 대해 들어보셨나요?

data.description: This service is for children who are not yet of school age and aims to prevent visual impairment.
data.conversation: Do you know of any services that provide support for young children to prevent visual impairment?
data.translation: 취학 전 아동의 시각 장애 예방을 위한 지원 서비스를 아시나요?

data.description: This service is for children under the age of 15, especially those from low-income families, who need preventive dental care and oral health education.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the dental care service for children under 15? I heard it's for those from low-income families as well.
data.translation: 15세 이하의 아이들을 위한 치과 관리 서비스에 대해 알려주세요.

data.description: This service is for registered disabled individuals who need comprehensive support and services based on their level of disability.

data.translation: 등록 장애인들을 위한 종합적인 지원과 서비스를 필요로 하는 사람들을 위한 이 서비스에 대해 설명해주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for individuals with severe disabilities who have a minimal income due to decreased work ability and face financial difficulties due to additional expenses related to their disability.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the welfare service for individuals with severe disabilities who have limited income and face financial difficulties?
data.translation: 중증 장애를 가진 소득이 적어진 사람들을 위한 복지 서비스에 대해 알려주세요.

data.description: This service is for parents or guardians of children with disabilities between the ages of 0-12 who have a welfare card. It provides financial support for childcare expenses.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the childcare support for children with disabilities? Who is eligible for this service and how can I apply?
data.translation: 장애아동의 어린이집 보육료 지원에 대해 알려주세요.

data.description: This service is for families with individuals who have developmental disabilities (intellectual or autism spectrum disorders), including those with children under the age of 6 who are not registered with disabilities but have a recent medical opinion (diagnosis) or a request for developmental rehabilitation services.

data.translation: 발달장애를 가진 개인들과 그 가족을 위한 지원 서비스가 있는지 알고 계신가요?

data.description: This service is for disabled children who are under 12 years old and use after-school daycare for more than 4 hours a day.
data.conversation: Do you know if there is any support available for disabled children who use after-school daycare for more than 4 hours a day?
data.translation: 일일 4시간 이상 방과후 어린이집을 이용하는 장애아동을 위한 지원이 있는지 알고 계신가요?

data.description: This service is for students with special educational needs who require therapy support in order to effectively receive education.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the service for students with special educational needs who require therapy support?
data.translation: 특수교육대상자가 교육을 효율적으로 받기 위해 치료지원이 필요한 학생들을 위한 서비스에 대해 말해주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for registered disabled individuals who want to receive information technology education and support.
data.conversation: Do you know if there are any free information technology education programs available for registered disabled individuals?
data.translation: 장애인들을 위한 무료 정보기술 교육 프로그램이 있는지 알고 계신가요?

data.description: This service is for individuals with severe disabilities who are in need of vocational rehabilitation support.
data.conversation: Can you tell me more about the vocational rehabilitation support for individuals with severe disabilities?
data.translation: 중증 장애를 가진 사람들을 위한 직업 재활 지원에 대해 더 알려주세요.

data.description: This service is for individuals with disabilities who are in need of purchasing products made by disabled individuals or who require assistance and support related to vocational rehabilitation facilities for disabled individuals.
data.conversation: Can you tell me more about the service for purchasing products made by disabled individuals or getting support from vocational rehabilitation facilities?
data.translation: 장애인 직업 재활 시설로부터 지원을 받기 위한 서비스에 대해 더 알려주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for individuals with severe disabilities who need to obtain a certificate of severe disability for employment and vocational services or for other legal purposes.
data.conversation: Can you tell me how to apply for a certificate of severe disability for employment and vocational services?
data.translation: 취업 및 직업 서비스를 위해 중증 장애인 확인서를 신청하는 방법을 알려주세요.

data.description: This service is for individuals with disabilities who are interested in or in need of vocational training and have passed the designated admission process.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the vocational training program for individuals with disabilities?
data.translation: 장애인을 위한 직업훈련 프로그램에 대해 말해주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for business owners who employ or want to employ people with disabilities and need financial support for the installation or purchase of facilities and equipment.
data.conversation: Can you tell me more about the financial support available for business owners who employ people with disabilities?
data.translation: 장애인을 고용하는 사업주들을 위해 시설과 장비의 설치 또는 구입을 위한 재정적 지원이 필요해요

data.description: This service is for employers or potential employers who have or want to hire disabled individuals, as well as disabled workers and disabled public officials.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the support for assistive devices for disabled individuals in the workplace?
data.translation: 장애인을 고용하거나 고용하려는 사업주, 장애인 근로자 및 장애인 공무원을 위한 서비스에 대해 말해주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for individuals with disabilities who have completed disability entrepreneurship education and are interested in starting a business or transitioning to a new industry. It provides support for leasing deposits for startup businesses in certain industries.
data.conversation: Can you tell me more about the support for leasing deposits for startup businesses for individuals with disabilities who have completed disability entrepreneurship education?
data.translation: 장애인 창업교육을 이수한 장애인들을 위한 창업점포 임차보증금 지원에 대해 더 알려주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for disabled individuals who are eligible for medical benefits and have a reduced burden of medical expenses.
data.conversation: Can you tell me who is eligible for the support of medical expenses for disabled individuals?
data.translation: 장애인 의료비 지원

data.description: This service is for individuals with disabilities who are in need of financial support for their basic living expenses, medical expenses, housing, and education. It also includes individuals who are undergoing reevaluation or applying for disability pensions, disability allowances, and disability child allowances.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the support provided for individuals with disabilities who are in need of financial assistance for their basic living expenses, medical expenses, housing, and education?
data.translation: 장애 정도 심사를 받으러 가는데 이를 위한 지원에 대해 말해주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for families who have adopted children with disabilities and need financial assistance for their medical expenses.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the financial assistance available for families who have adopted children with disabilities?
data.translation: 장애아동을 입양한 가족들이 의료비를 지원받을 수 있는 혜택에 대해 알려주시겠어요?

data.description: This service is for households with a total health insurance premium self-payment amount below 180% of the median income, and it provides developmental rehabilitation services for children under 18 years old with disabilities.
data.conversation: Can you tell me who is eligible for the developmental rehabilitation service and what it offers?
data.translation: 발달재활 서비스는 중위소득의 180% 이하인 가구와 18세 미만의 장애아동을 대상으로 하며, 누구에게 제공되고 어떤 서비스를 제공하는지 알려주실 수 있나요?

data.description: This service is for individuals with disabilities or elderly individuals who have difficulty with mobility and need access to preventive medical services.
data.conversation: Can you tell me about the disability-friendly health check-up service? Who is eligible for this service?
data.translation: 장애친화 건강검진 서비스에 대해 알려주세요. 이 서비스를 받을 자격이 있는 사람은 누구인가요?

data.description: This service is for disabled individuals between the ages of 6 and under 65 who have been assessed and determined to have a certain level of functional ability and independent living skills.
